izes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>There are seasons when you look at your own life and think, <em>I should be farther along than this.</em> Not in success, not in followers, but in interior solidity. You want to feel integrated, grounded, and consistent — yet some days your heart moves in different directions at once. You feel God strongly in some moments, and in others you feel scattered, restless, or pulled toward old habits that you thought were behind you.</p><p>Some days you feel like you’re watching yourself from the outside.<br>Other days, you’re just trying to stay steady.</p><p>And beneath it all is this subtle ache: <em>Why does my inner life feel like a borderland instead of a home?</em></p><p>There’s a line from St. Augustine that’s brutally honest and deeply comforting:<br><strong>“My weight is my love; wherever I am carried, it is my love that carries me.”</strong> (Confessions 13.9)</p><p>He didn’t mean love always lifts us upward.<br>He meant: <em>you move in the direction of what you actually love, not what you wish you loved.</em></p><p>Your desires, your fears, your wounds, your longing, …</p>"}